Introduction

Lee Da-in, known under her stage name Rora, is a South Korean singer and dancer under YG Entertainment. She is best known as the lead vocalist of the girl group BABYMONSTER which she debuted with on November 27, 2023 with the group's digital single "Batter Up".

Before becoming a YG Entertainment trainee, Rora used to be a Japanese idol. She debuted as a member of the kids girl group U.SSO Girl as U.Ha, currently the group has disbanded.
